JOHANNESBURG – Racism and transformation in rugby continue to be hot topics nearly a week after the Ashwin Willemse/SuperSport debacle. Former Springbok winger Willemse accused co-presenters Naas Botha and Nick Mallett of undermining him last Saturday. WATCH: Transformation Rugby Coalition speaks out on Willemse walkout Willemse also said he had been labelled a quota player throughout his career before he walked off set. The highly-controversial quota system forces various sports associations to include a certain number of black, coloured and Indian players in teams. Watch the video above for more on South Africa's quota controversies. AFP